  "lore": {
    "key": "Tbl_Unit_Desc_74",
    "english": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains.",
    "japanese": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains.",
    "korean": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains.",
    "chinese_simplified": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains.",
    "chinese_traditional": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains.",
    "spanish": "Taimanin, also known as 'Kaworu of the Steel Chain.' She formerly served the Nisha family of the Fuuma clan, but now she leads a group of Taimanin troops of her own.\n\nHer ninja art, Chain Art, allows her to summon chains from her palms. She can control the chains with her mind, which she skillfully uses to whip, snare, or strangle her enemies. Furthermore, the chains bear a curse where they become as heavy as their victim's sins; the more sins committed, the harder it is to break away from the chains."
  },
